# ================================================
# Motion–TimeSpace (MBT) Unification Derivations
# ================================================

# MBT Core Field Parameters:
# λ : Geometric Tension        → [M T⁻²]
# γ : Geometric Damping        → [T⁻¹]
# c : Maximum Flow Speed       → [L T⁻¹]

# ------------------------------------------------
# I. Derived Constants: ℏ and G
# ------------------------------------------------

# Planck's Constant (ℏ) from λ, γ, c
ℏ ≈ κ_ℏ · (λ c²) / γ³          # [M L² T⁻¹] 

# Newton's Gravitational Constant (G)
G ≈ κ_G · (c³ γ) / λ           # [L³ M⁻¹ T⁻²] 

# ------------------------------------------------
# II. Fine-Structure Constant (α)
# ------------------------------------------------

# Electromagnetic Coupling Equivalent
C_E ≈ κ_E · (λ c³) / γ³        # [M L³ T⁻²] 

# Fine-Structure Constant
α ≈ κ_α · (C_E) / (ℏ c)        # Dimensionless 

# ------------------------------------------------
# III. Planck Units (from λ, γ, c)
# ------------------------------------------------

# Planck Length (L_P)
L_P ≈ κ_L · c / γ              # [L] 

# Planck Time (T_P)
T_P ≈ κ_T · 1 / γ              # [T] 

# Planck Mass (M_P)
M_P ≈ κ_M · λ / (γ c)          # [M] 

# ------------------------------------------------
# IV. Cosmological Constant (Λ)
# ------------------------------------------------

# Vacuum Energy Curvature
Λ ≈ κ_Λ · γ² / c²              # [L⁻²] 

# ================================================
# Unified MBT Constants Summary Table
# ================================================

# Constant      | Description             | MBT Derivation
# ------------- | ------------------------| ------------------------------
# ℏ             | Quantum Action          | κ_ℏ · (λ c²) / γ³
# G             | Gravitational Curvature | κ_G · (c³ γ) / λ
# α             | EM Coupling Strength    | κ_α · (C_E) / (ℏ c)
# L_P           | Quantum Length Limit    | κ_L · c / γ
# T_P           | Quantum Time Limit      | κ_T · 1 / γ
# M_P           | Quantum Mass Scale      | κ_M · λ / (γ c)
# Λ             | Vacuum Energy Density   | κ_Λ · γ² / c²

